==English==

===Conjunction===
'''and/or'''

#Used to join two alternatives, A and B, to mean "A, or B, or both A and B"; in other words, to indicate that "[[inclusive or]]" is meant where "or" alone might be taken to mean "exclusive or".

====Synonyms====
*[[or]]

